Help
  git help revert

Discard chages in woring area
  git checkout .
  git checkout f1

Local 
  Stage
    git add .
  Unstage 
    git reset HEAD~1 f1
    git reset HEAD~1 .
    git reset HEAD~1 *
    move file from stage into working area
    only apply to commits to local
    Apply last n(1,2,3)
    cannot choose commit by random number

git revert
    It create a new commit

pushed commit
  Revert
    git reset --soft  HEAD~1
    git reset --hard  HEAD~1
    git reset --mixed HEAD~1

The git reset command 
  undo commits 
  remove previous commits from the repository
  reset the Git HEAD to an earlier commit. 

Undo a commit and redo

$ git commit ...              (1)
$ git reset --soft HEAD~1     (2)
$ edit                        (3)
$ git add ....                (4)
$ git commit -c ORIG_HEAD     (5)
####
git reset --soft HEAD~3
git rm -rf directory
git add directoryname

git reset  # Untag all files
git reset HEAD file1 # unstage

##
git reset --soft HEAD~1 # lose git history
git reset --hard HEAD~1 # keep git history in workspace

